name: Angelic Blessing
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 and gains flying until end of turn. (It can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Only the warrior who can admit mortal weakness will be bolstered by immortal strength.

name: Armored Pegasus
text: Flying
flavor: Asked how it survived a run-in with a bog imp, the pegasus just shook its mane and burped.

name: Bog Imp
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Don't be fooled by their looks. Think of them as little knives with wings.

name: Breath of Life
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Coercion
text: Target opponent reveals his or her hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card.
flavor: A rhino's bargain\n—Femeref expression meaning\n"a situation with no choices"

name: Counterspell
text: Counter target spell.

name: Disenchant
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.

name: Drudge Skeletons
text: {B}: Regenerate Drudge Skeletons. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)
flavor: "The dead make good soldiers. They can't disobey orders, they never surrender, and they don't stop fighting when a random body part falls off."\n—Nevinyrral, Necromancer's Handbook

name: Durkwood Boars
flavor: "And the unclean spirits went out, and entered the swine: and the herd ran violently . . . ."\n—The Bible, Mark 5:13

name: Eager Cadet
flavor: The enthusiasm of the young, sharpened by the discipline of a soldier.

name: Flame Spirit
text: {R}: Flame Spirit gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: "The spirit of the flame is the spirit of change."\n—Lovisa Coldeyes,\nBalduvian chieftain

name: Flight
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has flying.

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Giant Octopus
flavor: At the sight of the thing the calamari vendor's eyes went wide, but from fear or avarice none could tell.

name: Goblin Hero
flavor: "When you're a goblin, you don't have to step forward to be a hero—everyone else just has to step back"\n—Biggum Flodrot, goblin veteran

name: Hand of Death
text: Destroy target nonblack creature.
flavor: The touch of death is never gentle.

name: Hero's Resolve
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+5.
flavor: "Destiny, chance, fate, fortune—they're all just ways of claiming your successes without claiming your failures."\n—Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Inspiration
text: Target player draws two cards.
flavor: "Madness and genius are separated only by degrees of success."\n—Sidar Jabari

name: Knight Errant
flavor: ". . . Before honor is humility."\n—The Bible, Proverbs 15:33

name: Lava Axe
text: Lava Axe deals 5 damage to target player.
flavor: Meant to cut through the body and burn straight to the soul.

name: Llanowar Elves
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: One bone broken for every twig snapped underfoot.\n—Llanowar penalty for trespassing

name: Merfolk of the Pearl Trident
flavor: Are merfolk humans with fins, or are humans merfolk with feet?

name: Mons's Goblin Raiders
flavor: Just because they have a club doesn't mean they're organized.

name: Monstrous Growth
text: Target creature gets +4/+4 until end of turn.
flavor: The nightstalkers' little game of tease-the-squirrel suddenly took an unexpected turn.

name: Moon Sprite
text: Flying
flavor: "I am that merry wanderer of the night."\n—William Shakespeare,\nA Midsummer Night's Dream

name: Obsianus Golem
flavor: "The foot stone is connected to the ankle stone, the ankle stone is connected to the leg stone . . . ."\n—"Song of the Artificer"

name: Ogre Warrior
flavor: Assault and battery included.

name: Orcish Oriflamme
text: Attacking creatures you control get +1/+0.

name: Prodigal Sorcerer
text: {T}: Prodigal Sorcerer deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Occasionally members of the Institute of Arcane Study acquire a taste for worldly pleasures. Seldom do they have trouble finding employment.

name: Python
flavor: "How can you claim the gods are merciless when they robbed the snake of its limbs to give the other creatures a sporting chance?"\n—Hakim, Loreweaver

name: Rhox
text: You may have Rhox assign its combat damage as though it weren't blocked.\n{2}{G}: Regenerate Rhox. (The next time this creature would be destroyed this turn, it isn't. Instead tap it, remove all damage from it, and remove it from combat.)

name: Rod of Ruin
text: {3}, {T}: Rod of Ruin deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Royal Falcon
text: Flying
flavor: Hunter by instinct, weapon by training.

name: Samite Healer
text: {T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: Healers ultimately acquire the divine gifts of spiritual and physical wholeness. The most devout are also granted the ability to pass physical wholeness on to others.

name: Scathe Zombies
flavor:
"They groaned, they stirred, they all uprose,
Nor spake, nor moved their eyes;
It had been strange, even in a dream,
To have seen those dead men rise."
—Samuel Coleridge,
"The Rime of the Ancient Mariner"

name: Sea Eagle
text: Flying
flavor: Where air meets water, fish meets talon.

name: Shock
text: Shock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Lightning tethers souls to the world.\n—Kor saying

name: Soul Net
text: Whenever a creature dies, you may pay {1}. If you do, you gain 1 life.

name: Spined Wurm
flavor: "As it moved, the wurm's spines gathered up bits of flowstone, which took the shapes of dead villagers' heads. Each head spoke a single sound, but if taken together, they said, ‘Alas for the living.'"\n—Dal myth of the wurm

name: Stone Rain
text: Destroy target land.

name: Terror
text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Time Ebb
text: Put target creature on top of its owner's library.
flavor: Like the tide, time both ebbs and flows.

name: Trained Orgg
flavor: All orggs know how to kill; training teaches them what to kill.

name: Venerable Monk
text: When Venerable Monk enters the battlefield, you gain 2 life.
flavor: His presence brings not only a strong arm but also renewed hope.

name: Vizzerdrix
flavor: Its swamp cousin may be meaner, but the vizzerdrix is much bigger.

name: Wild Griffin
text: Flying
flavor: Two little goblins, out in the sun. Down came a griffin, and then there was one.

name: Willow Elf
flavor: The forest lives in the elf as the elf lives in the forest.

name: Wind Drake
text: Flying
flavor: "No bird soars too high, if he soars with his own wings."\n—William Blake,\nThe Marriage of Heaven and Hell
